title: Salad Of Lobster, Fennel And Beetroot With Savoury Blackcurrants
summary: Salad Of Lobster, Fennel And Beetroot With Savoury Blackcurrants is a gluten free and pescatarian recipe with 121 servings. One portion of this dish contains roughly 2g of protein, 15g of fat, and a total of 146 calories. For 46 cents per serving, this recipe covers 4% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. Only a few people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. If you have baby fennel, egg white, double cream, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 45 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 35%. This score is not so awesome. Similar recipes include Smoked trout salad with fennel, apple & beetroot, Salmon, Watercress, Fennel and Baby Beetroot Salad With Lemony "Caviar" Dressing, and Apple-Fennel Lobster Salad.

winePairing.pairingText: Chablis and Chardonnay are great choices for Lobster. Chablis is perfect with lobster, but a chardonny from other regions is bound to hit the spot too. The Albert Bichot Chablis Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Vaillons Premier Cru with a 4.2 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 38 dollars per bottle.
